{"lemma":"رَطْب","slug":"رَطْب","root":"ر.ط.ب","root_slug":"ر-ط-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ط-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رَطْب","root":"رطب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n15788","n15789","n15791","n15792","n15793","n15794"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%B7%D9%92%D8%A8"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"humid, moist"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"wet","examples":[{"text":"لَا تَكُنْ رَطْبًا فَتُعْصَرَ وَلَا يَابِسًا فَتُكْسَرَ","english":"Be flexible, but firm; Like an egg, if it's held too tightly, it breaks, and if it's held too loosely, it will slip from grasp."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"fresh and tender"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"cool"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"juicy"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"pliable of character"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ripened dates","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Biblical Hebrew רָטֹב (rɔṭoḇ)."},"ipa":["/ratˤb/","/ra.tˤib/","/ru.tˤab/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n15788","headword_ar":"رَطُبَ","root":"rTb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, MA, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTiba","text_ar":"رَطِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTuwbapN","text_ar":"رُطُوبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, MA, Msb, K) of the former verb (S, A, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTaAbapN","text_ar":"رَطَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[also of the former verb]; (MA, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, S, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, the contr. of what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA bis","text_ar":"يَا بِس"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAf~","text_ar":"جَافّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e., (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, moist, humid, succulent, sappy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"juicy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, MA, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender, to chew:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fresh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"green;"},{"kind":"text","text":"agreeably with the Pers. explanation,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taro$udo","text_ar":"تَرْشُدْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the MA: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supple, pliant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flexible:"},{"kind":"text","text":"all meanings well known, of frequent occurrence, and implied in the first of the explanations above, and in explanations of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTobN","text_ar":"رَطْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTiybN","text_ar":"رَطِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender,"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a branch, or twig, and of plumage, &c.: (K:) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trT~b","text_ar":"ترطّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as used in the L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eqd","text_ar":"عقد"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c., signifies the same.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTuwbapN","text_ar":"رُطُوبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[used as a simple subst.] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A quality necessarily involving facility of assuming shape and of separation and of conjunction."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTubato","text_ar":"رَطُبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a girl, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, sappy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supple;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTuba","text_ar":"رَطُبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a boy, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, sappy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supple;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"femininely soft"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supple:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTobN","text_ar":"رَطْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below. ―         -b3-  Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTuba lisaAniY","text_ar":"رَطُبَ لِسَانِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi*ikorika","text_ar":"بِذِكْرِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trT~b","text_ar":"ترطّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My tongue has become supple by mentioning thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has been much occupied by mentioning thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a well-known phrase: (see also 2:) it may also be used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my tongue has become refreshed"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moistened"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by mentioning thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*o","text_ar":"خُذْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA raTubato bihi yadaAka","text_ar":"مَا رَطُبَتْ بِهِ يَدَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take that by means"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1101},{"kind":"text","text":"frequent handling"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which thy hands have become supple"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what thou hast found to be profitable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"useful."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b4-  See also 4, in two places.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTiba","text_ar":"رَطِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He spoke what he had in his mind, right and wrong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"correct and erroneous."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTaba","text_ar":"رَطَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTobN","text_ar":"رَطْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A'Obeyd, S, A, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTuwbN","text_ar":"رُطُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A'Obeyd, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fed"},{"kind":"text","text":"a horse (or similar beast, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the trefoil called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTobap","text_ar":"رَطْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (A'Obeyd, S, A, K.) ―         -b2-  See also 2."}],"source_refs":["S","A","MA","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n15789","headword_ar":"رطّب","root":"rTb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taroTiybN","text_ar":"تَرْطِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTobN","text_ar":"رَطْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTiybN","text_ar":"رَطِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moist, humid, succulent, sappy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"juicy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender, to chew:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fresh, new,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"green:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supple, pliant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flexible:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as applied to a branch, or twig, and to plumage, &c.:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA bis","text_ar":"يَا بِس"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he moistened"},{"kind":"text","text":"a garment, or piece of cloth, (A, K, TA,) &c.; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArTb","text_ar":"ارطب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisaAniY bi*ikorika","text_ar":"لِسَانِى بِذِكْرِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA zilotu A^uroTibu","text_ar":"مَا زِلْتُ اُرْطِبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have not ceased to make my tongue supple by mentioning thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have not ceased to employ my tongue frequently in mentioning thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA zlt A^uraT~ibu Alx","text_ar":"ما زلت اُرَطِّبُ الخ"},{"kind":"text","text":": for] one says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA raT~aba","text_ar":"مَا رَطَّبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisaAniY bi*ikorika A_il~aA maA balalotaniY bihi mino bir~ika","text_ar":"لِسَانِى بِذِكْرِكَ اـِلَّا مَا بَلَلْتَنِى بِهِ مِنْ بِرِّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nothing has made my tongue to become supple by mentioning thee save what thou hast bestowed upon me of thy bounty"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A. [See also 1.])       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rT~b","text_ar":"رطّب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) inf. n. as above, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fed"},{"kind":"text","text":"people"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTab","text_ar":"رُطَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fresh ripe dates"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, A, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTaba","text_ar":"رَطَبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) You say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano A^aroTaba","text_ar":"مَنْ اَرْطَبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naxoluhu walamo yuraT~ibo xabuva fiEoluhu walamo yaTibo","text_ar":"نَخْلُهُ وَلَمْ يُرَطِّبْ خَبُثَ فِعْلُهُ وَلَمْ يَطِبْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He whose palm-trees have fresh ripe dates and he does not feed"},{"kind":"text","text":"people"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with such dates, his conduct is bad, and is not good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.)       -A3-  See also the next paragraph, in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","A","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n15791","headword_ar":"رَطْبٌ","root":"rTb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTiybN","text_ar":"رَطِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaAbisN","text_ar":"يَابِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAf~N","text_ar":"جَافٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e. (Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moist, humid, succulent, sappy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"juicy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, MA, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender, to chew:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fresh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(agreeably with the Pers. explanation,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taro","text_ar":"تَرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the MA,) or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"green;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to herbage: (TA:) or they signify, (Msb,) or signify also, (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) applied to a branch, or twig, and to plumage, (S, K,) &c.: (K:) [and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supple, pliant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flexible."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [All these meanings are well known, of frequent occurrence, and implied in the first of the explanations above.] The former occurs in a trad. as an epithet particularly applied to Any article of property [or of provisions]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is not stored up, and will not keep;"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as [most kinds of] fruits, and herbs, or leguminous plants: such, IAth says, fathers and mothers and children may eat and give away agreeably with approved usage, without asking permission; but not husbands nor wives [when it belongs to one of them exclusively], without the permission of the owner. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAriyapN raTobapN","text_ar":"جَارِيَةٌ رَطْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sappy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supple,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"girl,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young woman."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K, * TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gulaAmN raTobN","text_ar":"غُلَامٌ رَطْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A boy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sappy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supple,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"femininely soft"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supple."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN raTobN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ رَطْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supple, man."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi*ikorika","text_ar":"بِذِكْرِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisaAniY raTiybN","text_ar":"لِسَانِى رَطِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My tongue is become supple by mentioning thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it may also be used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my tongue is become refreshed"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moistened"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by mentioning thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A. [See also 1 and 2.]) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN raTobapN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ رَطْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A pliant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vitious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an unchaste, woman; a fornicatress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an adulteress."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) One says, in reviling,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA A@bona Alr~aTobapi","text_ar":"يَا ا@بْنَ الرَّطْبَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O son of the fornicatress"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adulteress"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA raTaAbi","text_ar":"يَا رَطَابِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaAmi","text_ar":"قَطَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)  [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O fornicatress"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adulteress,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raTaAbi","text_ar":"رَطَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", being indecl., as a proper name in this sense,] is said in reviling a woman or girl. (A, K.) ―         -b5-  [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHomilu AlHaTaba Alr~aToba","text_ar":"يَحْمِلُ الحَطَبَ الرَّطْبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:) : see 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hml","text_ar":"حمل"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayo$N raTobN","text_ar":"عَيْشٌ رَطْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A soft, a delicate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an easy, life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraA^a","text_ar":"قَرَاَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlquroA=na raTobFA","text_ar":"القُرْا=نَ رَطْبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He read,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recited, the Kur-án softly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gently; not with a loud voice."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA from a trad) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luw^oluw^N raTobN","text_ar":"لُوْلُوٌ رَطْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a metonymical expression, meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Brilliant pearls, beautiful, smooth in the exterior, and perfect in clearness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it does not denote the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTuwabp","text_ar":"رُطُوَبة"},{"kind":"text","text":"that is the contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yubuwsap","text_ar":"يُبُوسَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": and similar to this is the expression"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almanodalu","text_ar":"المَنْدَلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aTobu","text_ar":"الرَّطْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fresh and fragrant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fine, aloes-wood"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","A","MA","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n15792","headword_ar":"رُطْبٌ","root":"rTb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTubN","text_ar":"رُطُبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pasture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is juicy, fresh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"green:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"green pasture, consisting of herbs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"season called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and of trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shrubs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T, K, TA:) [each] a coll. gen. n.: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"green herbage in general:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) accord. to the Kifáyet el-Mutahaffidh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTobN","text_ar":"رُطْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fresh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"juicy, herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pasture;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) or, as some say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTobapN","text_ar":"رُطْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurofapN","text_ar":"غُرْفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [though this seems to be the n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTobN","text_ar":"رُطْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] has this last meaning; (Msb;) what is dry being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha$iy$","text_ar":"حَشِيش"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","A","Mgh","T","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n15793","headword_ar":"رُطَبٌ","root":"rTb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fresh ripe dates;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ripe dates"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before they become dry;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA;) also called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamorN raTiybN","text_ar":"تَمْرٌ رَطِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muroTibN","text_ar":"مُرْطِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muraT~ibN","text_ar":"مُرَطِّبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the dates so called are well known: (S:) [it is a coll. gen, n.:] n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh, Msb, K:) it is not a broken pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTabapN","text_ar":"رُطَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", being masc. [as well as fem.] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamorN","text_ar":"تَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA ruTabN","text_ar":"هٰذَا رُطَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"These are fresh ripe dates"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; whereas, if it were a broken pl., you would make it [only] fem.: (Sb, TA:) its pl. [of pauc.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroTaAbN","text_ar":"اَرْطَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riTaAbN","text_ar":"رِطَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the pl. of the n. un. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTabaAtN","text_ar":"رُطَبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) There are two sorts of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTab","text_ar":"رُطَب"},{"kind":"text","text":": one sort cannot be dried, and spoils if not soon eaten: the other sort dries, and is made into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajowap","text_ar":"عَجْوَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (Msb.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busorN","text_ar":"بُسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["A","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","S","Sb"]},{"entry_id":"n15794","headword_ar":"رُطُبٌ","root":"rTb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTobN","text_ar":"رُطْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}